==Annotations==
'''Naminedamine'''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') Bloom's corruption of the liturgical phrase ''In nomine Domini'' (''In the name of the Lord'').<ref>Gifford (1988) 294.<br>Thornton (1968) 241.</ref> During Paddy Dignam's Burial Service, Bloom had concocted the term ''Dominenamine'' ([[Annotations_to_James_Joyce's_Ulysses/Hades/100|100.01]]). Later, in this episode, he will be inspired to concoct a similar nonsense word by a line in ''The Croppy Boy'': [[Annotations_to_James_Joyce's_Ulysses/Sirens/272|272.20]]. Another variant, ''nominedomine'', occurs at [[Annotations_to_James_Joyce's_Ulysses/Sirens/277|277.37]].

