==Annotations==
'''the ''nec'' and ''non plus ultra'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') The Latin phrases ''nec plus ultra'' and ''non plus ultra'' both mean ''extreme point'', ''summit'', ''acme''.<ref>Gifford (1988) 336.</ref> The form ''nec plus ultra'' is commonly used in French, and ''ne plus ultra'' in English.<ref>[http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/126142 Oxford English Dictionary.]</ref>


