[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=317]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''the church of Saint Fiacre ''in Horto'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') [[w:Fiacre|Saint Fiacre]] is the patron saint of gardeners. ''In Horto'' is Latin for ''in a garden''. There was no Church of Saint Fiacre in Ireland in 1904; Fiacre's 7th-century hermitage Kilfiachra has given its name to a townland and a civil parish, both known as Kilferagh, in [[w:County Kilkenny|County Kilkenny]].<ref>Gifford (1988) 354.</ref>


