<br>
==Annotations==
'''''En ventre sa mère'''''{{spaces|5}}(''French'') ''In his mother's belly''.<ref>Gifford (1988) </ref> This archaic French phrase is still used in [[w:En ventre sa mere|English law]] to refer to a child who has not yet been born. J. J. O'Molloy, who uses the phrase, is an unemployed lawyer.

